<section id="JCR.DeveloperReference.Basic">
  <title>Basic usage</title>
  <highlights>
    <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          <emphasis role="bold"><link linkend="JCR.UsingJCR">Use JCR</link></emphasis>
        </para>
        <para>Instructions on how to use JCR, such as how to obtain a Repository object, JCR Session common considerations and
        JCR Application practices.</para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          <emphasis role="bold"><link linkend="JCR.NodeTypes">Node types</link></emphasis>
        </para>
        <para>Instructions on how to define node types in the Repository at the start-up time and register the node types.</para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          <emphasis role="bold"><link linkend="JCR.Namespaces">Namespace</link></emphasis>
        </para>
        <para>Instructions on how to define and alter namespace.</para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          <emphasis role="bold"><link linkend="JCR.SearchingRepositoryContent">Search repository content</link></emphasis>
        </para>
        <para>Instructions on how to use the searching function for repository content by providing with the detailed information on query lifecycle,
        query usecases, and XPath queries containing node names starting with a number.</para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          <emphasis role="bold"><link linkend="JCR.UseFulltextSearch">Use fulltext search</link></emphasis>
        </para>
        <para>Instructions on how to use fulltext search in eXo JCR.</para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          <emphasis role="bold"><link linkend="JCR.DeveloperReference.Basic.FAQs">Frequently asked questions</link></emphasis>
        </para>
        <para>A list of FAQs related to basic development.</para>
      </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>
  </highlights>

